OL,3,CVictory for 'local legend' Nelson in
OL,4,Cimmigration battle to remain
OL,6,FA man described as a 'local legend' on
OL,7,FMerseyside says he's 'overwhelmed'
OL,8,Fafter the Home Office backed down and
OL,9,Fgranted him leave to remain in the UK
OL,10,Fwhere he's lived for 46 years.
OL,12,FNelson Shardey says he is 'very, very
OL,13,Fhappy and relieved'.
OL,15,FHe was planning a legal challenge to
OL,16,Fthe Government after he was told he
OL,17,Fwas 'not British' and would not be
OL,18,Fallowed indefinite leave to remain
OL,19,Fwhen he applied for a passport in 2019.
